data.description: ALT TEXT: A vibrant advertisement in colors of red and gold for Lunar New Year, with a pastel-colored origami fortune teller, a cute Lunar New Year snake cartoon, and the text below. Stop by and join us for our event! Lunar New Year Healthy "Fortune Teller" Origami Making for Students with Disabilities and Disability Allies Open to Students with Disabilities & Disability Allies >> WHAT to expect: Welcome back to the Spring 2025 Term! ODS and Scarlet Arts RX invite students with disabilities and disability allies to an afternoon of origami and conversation. Bring a friend or meet someone new. We will be making paper fortune tellers and briefly talking about accommodations.In a relaxing environment, learn how to make a fortune teller (because Lunar New Year traditions incorporate "fortune" as a strong theme), but this fortune teller will have a fun "twist" (pun intended!) to help you keep healthy habits throughout the semester! Come craft, chat, and snack!  FREE event, no previous origami experience needed.   >> WHO will be there: Teaching led by an Scarlet Arts Rx artist. Light snacks provided by Office of Disability Services.   >> WHEN and WHERE it will be: Monday, Jan. 27th, 3:30 - 5pm Office of Disability Services Testing Center Livingston Apartments Building C, Room 105    >> OTHER items: Questions or event accommodations? Please email dsoffice@echo.rutgers.edu, call 848-202-3111, or visit ODS in Lucy Stone Hall, Suite A145.
data.location: Office of Disability Services Testing Center
